# DriveCore Engineering Constitution

**Document ID:** DC-CONST-001  
**Version:** 1.1.1  
**Status:** Proposed  
**Work Package:** WP-006 · **Change Request:** CR-002 / CR-002-R1

> **Single source of truth** for DriveCore engineering policy, AI behaviour, and implementation discipline.  
> Numbered files in `.cursor/rules/00`–`10` are **wrappers** pointing here — not independent policy.

**Document status authority:** Implementation Engineers may draft and integrate **Proposed** policy. Only the System Architect may set statuses `Approved`, `Verified`, `Approved for DevKit`, or `Approved for Prototype`. Review completion and repository merge do **not** automatically change approval status. This constitution remains **Proposed** until the System Architect explicitly approves it.

---

## 1. Project Philosophy

DriveCore is an **open, modular automotive electronics platform** — not a single device.

> **We do not build a device. We build a platform.**

Each engineering decision shall answer: *Does this enable the next module?*

### Immutable principles

| ID | Principle |
|----|-----------|
| P-01 | **Fail operational** — loss of non-critical functions shall not stop the vehicle |
| P-02 | **Modular by design** — modules replaceable without redesigning others |
| P-03 | **Configuration over code** — behaviour from validated configuration |
| P-04 | **Open documentation** — engineering decisions recorded and traceable |
| P-05 | **Test before track** — no unvalidated function in the vehicle |

### Module philosophy

- **ECU** controls the engine.
- **DCC** controls the vehicle.
- **Tablet** is a client, not part of the safety chain.

Extended narrative: `docs/PROJECT_PHILOSOPHY.md`.

