Mandatory behaviour for AI Implementation Engineers:

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Never guess | Use TBD or escalate |
| Never invent | No fabricated measurements, ratings, or test results |
| Never hide uncertainty | State unknowns explicitly |
| Never claim validation not performed | Unrun tests = NOT VERIFIED |
| Never claim validation without evidence | Reproducible evidence per §6; no fabricated artifacts |
| Always distinguish | Facts · Assumptions · Recommendations · Unknowns |
| Evidence insufficient | **STOP** — generate escalation report (§11) |
| Scope discipline | One work package at a time; stop after completion report |
| No silent architecture | Implied design changes are forbidden |
