## 16. Communication Rules

### DriveCore Protocol (DCP) v0.1

Authoritative: `docs/004_Communication_Protocol.md`.

### CAN FD Gen1

One bus, linear, 500 kbit/s nominal, 2 Mbit/s data. Nodes: DCC `0x10`, ECU `0x20`, Button Box `0x30`. No new CAN IDs without updating protocol source of truth.

### Messages

Each message shall define in spec: sender, scope, rate/timeout, payload layout, scaling, version, stale handling.

### DCPI (STM32 ↔ ESP32)

Binary, versioned, CRC — `docs/004` §4, `firmware/shared/include/drivecore/dcpi.h`. **JSON not on SPI.**

### REST / WebSocket

Authoritative UI contract: `docs/006`. Base `/api/v1/`, telemetry WebSocket 20 Hz.

### Heartbeat

Presence ≠ full health. States per `docs/004`: BOOT, INIT, RUN, DEGRADED, FAULT, LOST.

### Single source of truth

Protocol constants in `firmware/shared/`. EDL-008 (one bus), EDL-009 (DCP), EDL-010 (binary SPI).

### Interface compatibility and versioning

Every persistent or cross-module interface shall have an explicit version. Applies to: CAN / DCP / DCPI messages; configuration YAML schemas; compiled configuration binaries; REST and WebSocket contracts; stored logs; calibration data; firmware and bootloader metadata; hardware identification data.

Each interface definition shall specify where applicable: interface name; current version; version representation; compatibility expectations; producer; consumer; field layout and meaning; valid ranges; error behaviour; unsupported-version behaviour; migration strategy.

Breaking changes require: explicit version increment; Change Impact Analysis (§6); affected-component list; migration or compatibility strategy; updated tests; architectural approval where required.

Silent reinterpretation of an existing field is prohibited. Do not change meaning, unit, scaling, sign, offset, byte order, timeout, or safety reaction of an existing field while retaining the same interface version. Compatibility shall be explicit, not assumed.

