## 17. Safety Principles

### Layer safety ownership

| Layer | Safety role |
|-------|-------------|
| STM32 | Safety-relevant real-time, VCM, power enable chain, kill interaction |
| ESP32 | **Never safety-critical** |
| Tablet / Web UI | **Never required** for vehicle operation |
| ECU | Engine protection only; not body loads |

### Fail operational

ESP32, tablet, or Wi-Fi loss shall not stop engine, pumps, cooling execution per VCM/rules.

### Per-function safe state

Do **not** assume “all outputs OFF” is universally safe. Each function needs defined reaction for: ECU power · fuel pump · coolant pump · fans · lighting · EHPS · wipers · isolation circuits. Missing reaction → **OPEN ISSUE** / escalate.

### Kill / isolation

Competition battery-isolation and engine-stop shall not depend solely on STM32, ESP32, CAN, or Web UI.

### Configuration safety

Config shall not override hardware channel capability, current ceilings, PWM limits, retry limits, or revision compatibility.

### Testing gate

DevKit before vehicle (EDL-014). Fail-operational tests per `docs/008`.

