## 19. Definition of Done

A task is complete **only if:**

| Criterion | Required |
|-----------|----------|
| Documentation updated | Affected docs reflect changes |
| Traceability preserved | Requirement IDs, WP/CR references intact; chain per §6 |
| Cross-references verified | Links resolve; pointers consistent |
| No duplicated information | Policy not copied outside constitution |
| No unresolved contradictions | Conflicts escalated, not hidden |
| Architecture preserved | No unauthorized ADR-level changes |
| Change impact addressed | Impact Level 0/1/2 classified; required artifact completed |
| Validation completed | Honest report with reproducible evidence or NOT VERIFIED |
| Revision identity recorded | Sufficient baseline identity for any Verified claim |
| Completion report generated | All mandatory sections present; impact classification stated |
| No unauthorized engineering decisions | Escalations documented |
| No unauthorized status promotion | Architecture/policy approval unchanged without Architect; verification certification not self-assigned for high-impact work |

Then: **Stop.** Wait for review. No further work without new task.

