## 21. Anti-Patterns

The following practices are **prohibited:**

| Anti-pattern | Why forbidden |
|--------------|---------------|
| Selecting components before requirements | Violates decision hierarchy (§10) |
| Inventing datasheet values | Violates engineering integrity (§3) |
| Silently changing architecture | Violates architecture protection (§9) |
| Implementing before defining interfaces | Violates interface-first skill (§7) |
| Duplicating sources of truth | Creates conflicting policy |
| Replacing TBD with assumptions | Masks missing evidence |
| Freezing hardware before qualification | Violates qualification stage (§10) |
| Implementation defining architecture | Wrong role (§4) |
| Premature optimization | Before testing stage (§10) |
| Undocumented engineering decisions | Violates traceability (§3) |
| Inferring current from part numbers | Component selection anti-pattern |
| Claiming tests passed without execution | AI behaviour violation (§8) |
| Claiming validation without evidence | Evidence-backed validation (§6) |
| Testing an unidentified hardware or firmware revision | Baseline identity (§6) |
| Changing a shared interface without impact analysis | CIA required (§6) |
| Silently changing interface field meaning | Interface versioning (§16) |
| Changing an interface without version handling | Interface versioning (§16) |
| Implementing functions without requirement or task traceability | Orphan implementation (§6) |
| Marking unknown data as `N/A` | Documentation language (§13) |
| Using unitless engineering constants | Numeric discipline (§6) |
| Hiding magic numbers in safety-relevant code | Firmware / numeric discipline (§6, §14) |
| Treating implementer self-review as independent Critical Review | Review independence (§18) |
| Changing document approval status without authority | Status governance (§13) |
| Using a merged commit as proof of engineering approval | Status governance (§13) |
| Continuing past assigned task | Workflow violation (§12) |
| JSON on SPI between STM32 and ESP32 | Protocol violation (§16) |
| Hardcoding vehicle behaviour in firmware | Configuration principle (§1) |

